Rust equivalents found:
  - emString broadly maps to String (owned) and &str (borrowed)
  - The Rust codebase uses String/&str pervasively in the same roles as emString.
  - emString() -> String::new()
  - emString(const char*) -> String::from() or .to_string()
  - Get() / operator const char*() -> .as_str() or &str borrowing
  - GetLen()/GetCount() -> .len()
  - operator[] -> .as_bytes()[i] or .chars().nth(i)
  - Add / operator+= -> String::push_str() / format!()
  - operator+ -> format!() or + operator on String
  - Insert -> String::insert_str()
  - Replace -> String::replace() or String::replace_range()
  - GetSubString -> &str slicing or String::from(&s[a..b])
  - Remove -> String::drain() or String::replace_range(range, "")
  - Clear -> String::clear()
  - IsEmpty -> String::is_empty() or str::is_empty()
  - Comparison operators -> PartialEq, PartialOrd, Ord on String/&str (lexicographic)
  - Format/VFormat -> format!() macro
  - COW/GetDataRefCount/MakeNonShared -> no equivalent (String is single-owner)
  - GetWritable/SetLenGetWritable -> direct mutable access via &mut String
  Representative String/&str usage locations:
    - src/emCore/emListBox.rs:74,133,230,232 -- String for item text, name
    - src/emCore/emBorder.rs -- &str parameters for caption, description
